  "texts": [
    "Within the network, the relationship strengths (edge weights) are based on the number of patients sharing the same pair of diseases.",
    "Figure 4 displays the DCN created from the real-world bipartite data in Figure 2 after the application of a bipartite projection using the Jaccard similarity score.",
    "All edges of the network have been retained by using a default Jaccard similarity cut-off score of ≥0.",
    "Some node pairs are more strongly connected, such as in the Circulatory and Abnormal Findings Disease chapters and the Genitourinary and Endocrine chapters.",
    "This is due to the fact that many patients share these disease pairs."
  ],
